That is to say that this <a href="quarter%20period">quarter period</a> may be efficiently computed through the "agm",

Using this property of the AGM along with the ascending transformations of Landen, <a href="Richard%20P.%20Brent">Richard Brent</a> suggested the first AGM algorithms for the fast evaluation of elementary transcendental functions ("e", cos "x", sin "x"). Subsequently, many authors went on to study the use of the AGM algorithms.





